Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacity of magnesium gallate MgGa2O4was measured by adiabatic calorimetry (7-347 K)and differential scanning calorimetry (322-1200 K). Thermodynamic functions (heat capacity, entropy,enthalpy change and derived Gibbs energy) were calculated in the range 0 1200 K. Gibbs energy of forma-tion of MgGa2O4was estimated using the standard entropy S0(298.15 K) from this work: fG0(MgGa2O4,298.15 K) = -1594.3 +- 4.3 kJ mol-1. The Debye characteristic temperature D= 750 +- 20 K was calculatedfrom heat capacity data and from elastic constants.
Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic functions of magnesium gallate MgGa2O4 in thetemperature range 0-1200 K
